{"headline": "Pink Floyd\u2019s \u2018Comfortably Numb\u2019 and Other Takes", "body": "\n \n         \n\n \n         \n\n \n         \n\n \n         \n\nRoger Waters and David Gilmour of the iconic rock band Pink Floyd turned their riffs into  \nover their hit song \u201cComfortably Numb\u201d (the 1979 album \u201cThe Wall\u201d). Some fans took sides. Some stood by. But no matter which side of The Wall you\u2019re on, the song\u2019s message is universal: Chances are you\u2019ve become comfortably numb to something in life, in order to cope.         \n\n\u201cNumb\u201d was written as a conversation between doctor and patient, coping with worldly demons and pain. Many have covered it, including Eddie Vedder of Pearl Jam, Van Morrison, Dar Williams and Ani DiFranco, and the pop band Scissor Sisters (videos below).         \n\nAfter creative differences led to Mr. Waters\u2019s split from the band and a notorious  \n, Mr. Waters and Mr. Gilmour  \n onstage in London in July 2005.         \n\nOn Wednesday night at Madison Square Garden, Roger Waters will be one of the performers honoring wounded veterans at the seventh annual  \n event.         \nDavid Gilmour - Comfortably Numb Live 1986 \nRoger Waters, Van Morrison, The Band - Comfortably Numb \n*High Quality Sound* Comfortably Numb feat. Roger Waters and Eddie Vedder \nScissor Sisters - comfortably numb (T Park) \nComfortably Numb - Dar Williams & Ani DiFranco \n\n \n         \n\n \n         \n\nA  \n         \n\n \n         \n\nVery  \n        ", "url": "http://www.nytimes.com/2013/11/05/booming/pink-floyds-comfortably-numb-and-other-takes.html", "date": "2013-11-05", "description": "The universal message of  Pink Floyd\u2019s hit song \u201cComfortably Numb\u201d has inspired many to cover it."}